==Spanish==

===Etymology 1===
Latin ''[[dicam]]'', present subjunctive form of ''[[dicere]]''

===Verb form===
'''diga'''

# present subjunctive first person singular form of ''[[decir]]'': may I say

===Etymology 2===
Latin ''[[dicat]]'', present subjunctive form of ''[[dicere]]''

===Verb form===
# present subjunctive third person (or second person formal) singular form of ''[[decir]]'': may it/you say, may it/you tell
# polite singular imperative: say, tell.
# way to say [[hello]] on the [[telephone]]
#: "Diga." ("Talk"); "Dígame." ("Talk to me.", "Say something to me.")

====Synonyms====
*[[bueno]] (3)

